TextChange: I see this with lottery winners.  They win big at the lottery, and then immediately quit their jobs and go on shopping sprees, purchasing all the things they never could have in the past.  In the moment, they are about as happy as can be.  But, what happens when the lottery winnings dry up?  They'll be back to where they started, only this time they'll have all these fancy things and no place to use them.   => I
And, if you're not happy with yourself now, then you'll never be happy. => W
